&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CROYDON HEALTH SERVICES NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant Diabetes and Endocrinologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of a full time substantive Consultant in Diabetes and Endocrinology at Croydon Health Services NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Croydon University Hospital (CUH) is a large urban DGH serving a diverse population of 380,000 in South London. Croydon Health Services is one of the largest employers in the London Borough of Croydon and has integrated with community services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers the successful candidate an opportunity to develop the new diabetes community service with another 2 consultant colleagues. The post holder will join a team of four Consultant Endocrinologists in providing outpatient diabetes and endocrinology clinics, and inpatient general (internal) medicine (GIM) care. The post-holder will contribute to a GIM ward round. The appointee will offer clinical leadership for all aspects of the service including service development, quality assurance and training, and contribute to productive interaction with primary care providers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from candidates who possess (or are within 6 months of acquiring) specialist accreditation in Diabetes and Endocrinology (CCT or equivalent).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested applicants are invited to contact Dr Ling Ling Chuah (Integrated Diabetes Community Lead), or Dr Sanjay Kumar (Clinical Lead) via switchboard on 0208 401 3000 at CUH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TBC&lt;/p&gt;
